  <!-- Government Origin Story Pattern -->
  <IdeoStoryPatternDef>
    <defName>Arktos_GovernmentOriginStory</defName>
    <segments>
      <li>intro</li>
      <li>hardship</li>
      <li>response</li>
      <li>legacy</li>
    </segments>
    <rules>
      <include>
        <li>IdeoDescriptionGlobal</li>
      </include>
      <rulesStrings>
        <li>intro->After the Great War, survivors banded together to form new governments, tribes, and gangs to endure the wasteland.</li>
        <li>hardship(uses=1)->They faced raiders, famine, storms, and the collapse of old laws.</li>
        <li>hardship(uses=1)->Tribal bands and city-states clashed over resources and territory.</li>
        <li>hardship(uses=1)->Corrupt rulers and warlords rose and fell, shaping the fate of settlements.</li>
        <li>response->Some built councils and assemblies, others followed chiefs, kings, or warlords.</li>
        <li>response->Tribes and gangs adapted, trading, raiding, or forging alliances to survive.</li>
        <li>response->Religions and cults grew, offering hope and order in chaos.</li>
        <li>legacy->From these struggles, new societies emerged—democratic, despotic, tribal, and raider—each with their own laws and customs.</li>
        <li>legacy->The wasteland remembers the rise and fall of many, but the strongest endure and shape the future.</li>
      </rulesStrings>
    </rules>
  </IdeoStoryPatternDef>
